      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "const movers = items.map(i => i.json);\n\nconst moverList = movers.map(m => {\n  const headlines = m.articles.map(a => `- ${a.headline}`).join('\\n');\n  return `${m.symbol}:\\n${headlines}`;\n}).join('\\n\\n');\n\nconst prompt = `You are writing a short, factual market recap for a personal daily portfolio digest. Below are today's biggest movers (±3% or more) and recent headlines about each.\n\nFor each ticker, write 2-3 sentences explaining the most likely reason for today's move, based ONLY on the headlines given. Include relevant specifics from the headlines (numbers, names, events) rather than staying vague. If the headlines don't clearly explain the move, say so honestly rather than guessing (e.g. \"No clear catalyst found in today's headlines\").\n\nThen write one short opening paragraph (4-5 sentences) summarizing the day's biggest story across all movers, mentioning the relevant tickers by symbol.\n\nMovers and headlines:\n${moverList}\n\nRespond ONLY in this exact JSON format, no other text:\n{\n  \"summary\": \"opening paragraph here\",\n  \"explanations\": {\n    \"TICKER1\": \"one sentence here\",\n    \"TICKER2\": \"one sentence here\"\n  }\n}`;\n\nreturn [{ json: { prompt } }];"
